---
hero:
  title: Driving Better Decisions and Business Performance with Unified Metrics
  subtitle: |-
    **dyvenia** is a professional company dedicated to turning fragmented data into clear, actionable insights. With deep industry expertise and proven frameworks, we simplify complexity. 

    By identifying gaps, aligning metrics, and integrating key data sources, we empower businesses to drive performance, foster alignment, ensure compliance, and optimize costs.
  button_text: Let's connect
  button_target: https://meetings-eu1.hubspot.com/alessio-civitillo/book-a-call
intro:
  title: Are your metrics designed to drive business performance?
  content: |-
    Many business leaders struggle to establish a performance-driven culture due to inconsistent metric definitions, fragmented dashboards, and a lack of detailed insights. Without a unified view, they are forced to rely on disconnected reports, ad hoc presentations, and informal communication to evaluate performance and make decisions. 

    Performance-driven enterprises overcome these challenges by prioritizing unified, trusted metrics—granular, auditable, and consistent across time, currencies, and organizational changes. These metrics align teams, provide clarity and confidence, and enable swift, informed decision-making that drives results.
highlight_one:
  title: We help business leaders cultivate a performance-driven culture with data
  subtitle: by helping with developing a clear data narrative, driving the adoption of unified metrics, and integrating flexible data marts tailored to fit seamlessly into your IT ecosystem. Through targeted training and established methodologies, we help bridge the gap between daily challenges and strategic opportunities.
highlight_two:
  title1: The Big Picture?
  title2: Unified, , Clear Metrics That Drive Performance
  content: Too often, analytics initiatives fall short of their promises. Complex models built without a deep understanding of business leave organizations with convoluted outputs instead of actionable insights. What businesses truly need are simple, transparent metrics that align teams and guide performance—metrics that deliver clarity and results.
foundations_titles:
  title1: The 5 unified metrics
  title2: attributes
foundations_elements:
  - title: In-Depth
    content: Granular drill-downs across key dimensions
  - title: Trust & Compliance
    content: Auditable metrics and models, no "black boxes"
  - title: Aligned
    content: Decision makers across the company agree on definitions
  - title: Comparable
    content: Metrics can be compared after reinstatements and org changes
  - title: Usability
    content: Clean, consistent, and enriched data and metrics for analysis
about:
  title: About us
  content: |-
    We believe data-driven should be defined with concrete steps and connected with measuring and driving business performance.

    With a combined 30+ years of experience in data analytics, finance, and sales analytics, we are on a mission to help business leaders establish a performance-driven culture measured with objective data and metrics.
whyus_intro:
  title: Why do clients come to us?
  content: Business leaders lacking unified metrics suffer from one or more of these **11 challenges**
whyus_elements:
  - title: Slow Insights.
    content: Waiting a very long time to receive critical business insights.
  - title: Lack of Alignment
    content: Spending time and resources to review numbers that do not match.
  - title: Lack of Trust.
    content: Managers across the organization not trusting the data and metrics.
  - title: Misusing Talent.
    content: Having many analysts and professionals wasting time on manually creating and managing reports.
  - title: Increasing tech debt.
    content: Creating custom logic across reports and dashboards that is understood only by a few.
  - title: Lack of integrated planning.
    content: Planning is not integrated across departments, generating obsolete inventory and other issues.
  - title: Impossible comparisons.
    content: Comparisons become impossible due to org changes, and reinstatements of standard costs, currencies, etc.
  - title: Poor Usability.
    content: Metrics are hard to access, data is hard to use, very hard to build ad-hoc analysis quickly
  - title: Struggling with best practices.
    content: Lacking guidance in what it takes to build good and unified metrics, data initiatives become expensive mistakes
  - title: Difficulty in retaining key talent.
    content: Experiencing challenges in keeping team members motivated
  - title: Difficulty in onboarding talent.
    content: Experiencing challenges when onboarding new analysts to the complex web of reports and data assets in use
our_services:
  title: Our Solutions
our_services_items:
  - title: The Plan & MVP
    prefix: Developing
    description: We begin by analyzing your business strategy to identify gaps in your current metrics, leveraging workshops and interviews with key business leaders. From there, we craft a compelling narrative to articulate the purpose and value of the metrics initiative. Finally, we develop a comprehensive roadmap, including a detailed resource plan, to ensure successful execution and we deliver a Minimum Viable Product to show feasibility.
  - title: The Execution
    prefix: Optional
    description: We implement the roadmap by assembling a dedicated team of data analysts, solution architects, and a project manager. This team ensures seamless communication across all levels while maintaining direct engagement with business leaders to align on goals and priorities.
description: Eleventy starter using modern CSS, fluid type, fluid spacing, flexible layout and progressive enhancement.
bodyClass: home
blog:
  title: Our Insights
  intro: Selected Articles. Check our blog for more.
layout: base
permalink: /index.html
title: The Scalable Way
---
<div class="wrapper">
  <div class="hero | wrapper">
    <header class="flow">
      <h1>{{ hero.title }}</h1>
      {{ hero.subtitle | markdownFormat | safe }}
      <a href="{{ hero.button_target }}" class="button"> {{ hero.button_text }} {% svg "misc/arrow" %}</a>
    </header>
    {% svg "brand/simple" %}
    {% svg "brand/staggered" %}
  </div>
</div>

<div class="intro | wrapper">
  <article class="region flow prose">
    <h2 class="text-step-2">{{ intro.title }}</h2>
    {{ intro.content | markdownFormat | safe }}
  </article>
</div>

<div class="highlight-one | wrapper">
  <div class="full wrapper section" style="--spot-color: var(--color-blue-accent)">
    <article class="full  intro | section__inner wrapper  region">
      <div class="feature flow prose">
        <h2 class="text-step-3">{{ highlight_one.title }} <span>*</span></h2>
        <p class="text-step-min-1"><span>*</span> {{ highlight_one.subtitle }}</p>
      </div>
      {% svg "brand/rings" %}
    </article>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="highlight-two | wrapper">
  <div class="full wrapper section" style="--spot-color: var(--color-dove-gray-700)">
    <article class="full  intro | section__inner wrapper region flow prose text-center text-dove-gray-50">
      <h2 class="text-step-2">
        {{ highlight_two.title1 }}
        <span class="block text-step-3 text-pink">{{ highlight_two.title2 }} </span>
      </h2>
      <p>{{ highlight_two.content }}</p>
    </article>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="foundations | wrapper">
  <article class="full region flow">
    <h2 class="text-step-3 text-center">
      {{ foundations_titles.title1 }}
      <span class="block uppercase text-royal-blue-500">{{ foundations_titles.title2 }} </span>
    </h2>
    <div class="split region">
      {% svg "brand/brick" %}
      <ol class="timeline">
        {% for key in foundations_elements %}
          <li>
            <span>{{ loop.index }}</span>
            <div class="flow flow-space-3xs">
              <h3 class="text-step-1">{{ key.title }}</h3>
              <p>{{ key.content }}</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        {% endfor %}
      </ol>
    </div>
  </article>
</div>

<div class="about | wrapper">
  <article class="feature | region">
    <header class="grid" data-layout="thirds">
      <h2>{{ about.title }}</h2>
      <div class="flow">{{ about.content | markdownFormat | safe }}</div>
    </header>
    <div class="grid region" data-layout="thirds">
      {% for member in team.admin %}
        <div class="about__content flow">
          {% image "." + member.image, "" %}

          <h3>{{ member.name }}</h3>
          {{ member.description_short | markdownFormat | safe }}
        </div>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </article>
</div>

<div class="why | wrapper">
  <article class="feature | region flow">
    <header class="flow">
    <h2>{{ whyus_intro.title }}</h2>
      {{ whyus_intro.content | markdownFormat | safe }}
      </header>

      <dl class="flow region column" role="list">
        {% for key in whyus_elements %}
          <div class="flow">
            <dt class="font-bold text-pink">{{ key.title }}</dt>
            <dd>{{ key.content }}</dd>
          </div>
        {% endfor %}
      </dl>
  </article>
</div>

<div class="services | wrapper">
  <div class="full wrapper section" style="--spot-color: var(--color-blue-accent)">
    <article class="full intro | section__inner wrapper region flow">
      {% svg "brand/arrows" %}
        <h2 class="text-center">{{ our_services.title }}</h2>
        <div class="mt-m">
          {% for item in our_services_items %}

            <div class="grid" data-layout="thirds">
              <h3>{{ item.prefix }} <span>{{ item.title }}</span></h3>
              <div>
              {{ item.description | markdownFormat | safe }}
            </div>
            </div>

          {% endfor %}
    </article>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="wrapper">
  <section class="full | region">
    <div class="wrapper flow prose">
      <h2>{{ blog.title }}</h2>

      {% if blog.intro %}
        <p>{{ blog.intro }}</p>
      {% endif %}

      <div class="feature |  region">
        <custom-masonry layout="50-50">

                   <!-- loop posts -->
         {% set itemList = collections.allPosts %}
         {% asyncEach item in itemList.slice(0, 4) %}
           {% set definedDate = item.date %}
           {% include "partials/card-blog.njk" %}
         {% endeach %}

        </custom-masonry>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>

{%- css "inline" -%}
  {%- include 'css/home.css' -%}
  {%- include 'css/column.css' -%}
  {%- include "css/custom-card.css" -%}
{%- endcss -%}
